        <scopecontent id="ref9">
            <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
            <p>The 
                <emph render="italic">New York Review</emph> Archive is a collection of correspondence to the editor Peter McCurtain from 1957 to 1958. The correspondence is predominantly made-up of notes from authors who are declining a contribution to the magazine. However, the collection highlights a wide array of correspondents, including: Ray Bradbury, Arthur C. Clarke, Aldous Huxley, Noel Coward, John F. Kennedy, Alec Guinness, C.S. Lewis, Harry Brown, Norman Mailer, Margaret Mead, James A. Michener, J.D. Salinger, E.E. Cummings, Robert Penn Warren, among many others.</p>
            <p>SERIES DESCRIPTION</p>
            <p>Series I: Correspondence: includes a copy of the 
                <emph render="italic">New York Review</emph> (box 1, folder 1).</p>
        </scopecontent>
